International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 7 Apr 2011
Source: ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation) Rural
[edited]
http://www.abc.net.au/rural/news/content/201104/s3184825.htm


Mosquitoes blamed for horse deaths
----------------------------------
Mosquito-borne viruses have been identified as the killers of scores
of horses across eastern Australia.

Tests done by the Victorian Department of Primary Industries [DPI]
found Murray Valley encephalitis and Ross River viruses were
responsible for the outbreak.

To date, 18 horse deaths are confirmed in Victoria, and from more
than 110 cases reported in New South Wales, about 15 died or had to be
euthanised.

Victoria's deputy chief vet Andrew Cameron says the worst of the
outbreak is over.

"A number of exotic diseases were ruled out in this case and a lot of
hendravirus testing was also done and ruled out at the Animal Health
Laboratory at Geelong," he said.

"We used the DPI laboratory which has a very strong arbovirus
investigation capability as well."

