[While Ross River and Murray Valley encephalitis viruses were
diagnosed, one wonders what happened to the diagnosis of Kunjin virus.
It seemed at some point they were all on the list of diagnostic rule
outs.

In other postings I have inquired what test method was used for the
diagnosis. Was it PCR? Was it serology? Is there any cross reactivity
in the testing? How many viruses were tested for? - Mod.TG]

